summary: Southwest Airlines is a big U.S. airline that flies to 121 places in the U.S. and 10 other countries. It started in 1967 in Texas and now has the most passengers in the U.S. and is the third largest in the world. It's different because it doesn't charge for checked bags and uses mostly Boeing 737 planes. Southwest has about 66,000 workers and flies to places in 42 states and Central America.
title: Southwest Airlines
